# ============================================================
# Harness-repo-specific gitignore additions (Public Release Hardening plan)
# See docs/plans/public-release-hardening.md and principles/harness-hygiene.md.
#
# Neural Lace is a harness repo that publishes publicly. These patterns
# prevent per-project operational artifacts from accumulating identifiers
# of the projects the harness was used to build.
#
# NOTE: normal project repos using Neural Lace as a template should NOT
# copy these rules. Projects SHOULD commit their plans, decisions, reviews,
# and session summaries — those are team-shared permanent records.
# ============================================================

# Private keys + certificates (defense-in-depth; scanner catches too)
*.pem
*.p12
*.pfx
id_rsa
id_rsa.pub
id_ed25519
id_ed25519.pub

# Operational artifacts
#
# Neural Lace is itself a project with its own development work. PLANS
# for improving neural-lace belong in the repo and get committed like
# any project's artifacts — the denylist scanner catches identifier
# leakage in those committed plans.
#
# Decisions, reviews, sessions, and SCRATCHPAD remain local-only for now:
# decisions/reviews might reference incident detail that's hard to sanitize,
# sessions are ephemeral transcripts, and SCRATCHPAD is per-session working
# state. Promote individual entries to harness-architecture.md or best-practices.md
# if they merit a permanent, sanitized record.
#
# What is NEVER committed: plan/decision/review/session files that were
# produced while USING neural-lace to build something else — those belong
# in the downstream project's own repo, not here.
SCRATCHPAD.md

# docs/{decisions,reviews,sessions}: ignore content that doesn't follow the
# established NL-self conventions. Decision records are NNN-*.md; reviews
# and sessions are YYYY-MM-DD-*.md. Anything else under these paths is
# treated as downstream-project artifact and gitignored. This closes
# HARNESS-GAP-10 sub-gap H — legitimate NL-self artifacts commit normally
# without `git add -f`, while downstream-project content remains protected.
# (Per git's gitignore quirk: cannot re-include files if their parent
# directory is excluded; therefore we exclude file patterns inside each
# directory rather than the directories themselves.)
docs/decisions/*
!docs/decisions/[0-9][0-9][0-9]-*.md
docs/reviews/*
!docs/reviews/[0-9][0-9][0-9][0-9]-[0-9][0-9]-[0-9][0-9]-*.md
docs/sessions/*
!docs/sessions/[0-9][0-9][0-9][0-9]-[0-9][0-9]-[0-9][0-9]-*.md

# Pre-sanitization plan files (committed before the "track our own plans"
# convention was settled; contain test data / denylist patterns that the
# scanner flags). These remain local-only. Sanitize first if you want to
# commit them. Both active and archive paths are excluded — the
# plan-status-archival-sweep hook (2026-05-04) moves terminal-status plans
# into archive/, but unsanitized content stays local regardless.
docs/plans/document-freshness-system.md
docs/plans/document-freshness-system-evidence.md
docs/plans/public-release-hardening.md
docs/plans/public-release-hardening-evidence.md
docs/plans/archive/document-freshness-system.md
docs/plans/archive/document-freshness-system-evidence.md
docs/plans/archive/public-release-hardening.md
docs/plans/archive/public-release-hardening-evidence.md

# Local user config surface (new in Phase 3)
# ~/.claude/local/ is a user-home path, but shadow any local mirror here:
.claude-local/

# Session ephemera written by hooks at runtime (2026-05-04). Includes:
# - .claude/state/acceptance/ (Generation 5 end-user-advocate runtime artifacts)
# - .claude/state/autonomous-done-*.txt (narrate-and-wait-gate session-end attestations)
# - .claude/state/scope-waiver-*.txt (per-session scope-enforcement-gate waivers)
# - .claude/state/user-goals/ (UserPromptSubmit goal extraction artifacts)
# - .claude/state/reviews/ (plan-evidence-reviewer audit trails)
# All per-session ephemeral; never committed. Specific subdirs (acceptance/)
# are documented in adapters/claude-code/agents/end-user-advocate.md.
.claude/state/

# Agent tool's isolated-worktree storage (per `isolation: "worktree"` in
# the orchestrator pattern). Each parallel-mode dispatch creates a worktree
# under .claude/worktrees/agent-<id>/ that contains a full repo checkout.
# Never committed; cleaned up by the Agent tool when the spawned agent
# makes no changes (worktrees with commits persist until cherry-pick).
.claude/worktrees/

# Moved to .example (Phase 4 scrub)
adapters/claude-code/business-patterns.paths
